Memory Usage: 14.3 MB, less than 33.96% of Python3 online submissions for Check If Two String Arrays are Equivalent.

Java:
class Solution {
    public boolean arrayStringsAreEqual(String[] word1, String[] word2) {
        String first_word = "";
        String second_word = "";
        for(int i = 0; i <word1.length;i++){
            first_word+=word1[i];
        }
        for(int i = 0; i <word2.length;i++){
            second_word+=word2[i];
        }
        
        if(first_word.equals(second_word)){
            return true;
        }
        else{
            return false;
        }
        
    }
}
